===Etymology===
Recorded since 1555, from {{etyl|es}} {{term|guaya|lang=es}}, a variant of {{term|guayaba|lang=es}}, from {{etyl|awd}} {{term|guayabo||guava tree}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɡwɑvə/}}
* {{rhymes|ɑːvə}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A tropical [[tree]] or [[shrub]] of the [[myrtle]] family, ''[[psidium guajava]]''.
# Its yellowish [[tropical]] [[fruit]], 1¼ to 2 inches, [[globular]] or [[pear]]-shaped with thin, yellow, green or brown [[skin]], is often made into [[jam]]s and [[jelly|jellies]]. The [[meat]] is yellowish or pale green to pink in color.

